'''Bada Valley''' or '''Napu Valley''', located in the [[Lore Lindu National Park]] in Central [[Sulawesi]], Indonesia, contains hundreds of [[megalith]]s going back to the 14th century that are called ''watu'' ("stone") in the local [[Badaic language]] and ''arca'' ("statue") in Indonesian. The purpose of the megaliths and their builders are unknown.
