{{Infobox lake | name = Baitings Reservoir | image = Baitings Dam - geograph.org.uk - 1226204.jpg | caption = View from Great Manshead Hill | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[West Yorkshire]] | coords = {{coord|53|39|57|N|1|59|25|W|type:waterbody_region:GB|display=inline,title}} | type = [[reservoir]] | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = United Kingdom | date-built = 1956 | length = {{convert|3250|ft|m}} | width = {{convert|1035|ft|m}} | area = | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | islands = | cities = }} '''Baitings Reservoir''' is a large water supply reservoir operated by [[Yorkshire Water]] close to [[Ripponden]] in the [[West Yorkshire]] [[Pennines]]. It lies in the valley of the [[River Ryburn]] and is the higher of two reservoirs built to supply [[Wakefield]] with water and was completed in 1956.<ref>[http://www.yorkshirewater.com/recreation/?OBH=53&SCH=baitings%20dam&ID=2078 Baitings Reservoir, Yorkshire Water.] Retrieved 24 February 2009.</ref> The lower reservoir is [[Ryburn Reservoir]].
