[[File:Fingrid logo.svg|thumb|Fingrid logo]]
'''Fingrid Oyj''' is a [[Finland|Finnish]] national [[electrical grid|electricity transmission grid]] operator. It is owned by the Finnish state (53.1 %) and various financial and insurance institutions (46.9 %).<ref>[http://www.fingrid.fi/en/investors/shares/Pages/default.aspx Shares and shareholders], Fingrid</ref> In 2011, power companies [[Fortum]] Power and Heat Oy and [[Pohjolan Voima]] sold their stakes in Fingrid (25% each), because of EU Internal Market Directive in Electricity, which requires that power production and ownership of the transmission systems should be separate. CEO of the company is Jukka Ruusunen.

