{{Infobox scientist | name = Tadahiko Mizuno | image = Dr. Tadahiko Mizuno in 2008.jpg | caption = Tadahiko Mizuno in 2008 | birth_date = 1945<ref name=ReaD&Researchmap /> | birth_place = [[Asahikawa, Hokkaido]], Japan<ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]" /> | death_date = | death_place = | spouse = | residence = Japan | citizenship = Japan | ethnicity = | fields = [[Nuclear fusion]]<ref name=ReaD&Researchmap /><ref name=KAKEN>{{cite web|last=KAKEN|title=Database of Grants-in-Aid for Scientific Research|url=http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/d/r/90002203|work=Researchers|publisher=2005-2013 National Institute of Informatics|accessdate=17 February 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130413132843/http://kaken.nii.ac.jp/d/r/90002203|archivedate=13 April 2013|df=}}</ref> | workplaces = | alma_mater = | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | notable_students = | known_for = [[Cold fusion]],<ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]" /> [[nuclear transmutation]]<ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]" /> | awards = [[The International Society for Condensed Matter Nuclear Science Prizes]] ([[Giuliano Preparata]] medal) in 2004<ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]" /><ref name="Giuliano Preparata Medal" /> | signature = }}
{{Nihongo|'''Tadahiko Mizuno'''|水野 忠彦|Mizuno Tadahiko|born 1945}} is a Japanese nuclear-chemist known for his work on [[cold fusion]].<ref name="Low-Energy Nuclear Reactions Sourcebook" /> He was a former assistant professor teaching the Atomic Power Environmental Materials program at [[Hokkaido University]].<ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]">{{cite book|last=Mizuno|first=Tadahiko|title=Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion|year=1998|publisher=Cold Fusion Technology|location=US|isbn=978-1-892925-00-8|pages=152}}</ref><ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]" /><ref name=KAKEN /><ref name=ICCF-17>{{cite web|last=The 17th International Conference on Cold Fuision|title=Biography_Dr. Tadahiko Mizuno|url=http://www.iccf17.org/popup/bio_11.htm|work=ICCF-17|publisher=ICCF-17 Secretariat|accessdate=14 February 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130415090253/http://www.iccf17.org/popup/bio_11.htm|archivedate=15 April 2013|df=}}</ref><ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion" /> He was also a member of Energy Environmental Institute of Engineering at Hokkaido University until 2009.<ref name=ICCF-17 />
==Early life== Mizuno graduated from the Department of Applied Physics, Hokkaido University, Faculty of Engineering in March 1968.<ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]" /><ref name="Low-Energy Nuclear Reactions Sourcebook" /><ref name=ICCF-17 /><ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion" /> In March 1970, he graduated with a master's degree from the Department of Applied Physics, Hokkaido University, Faculty of Engineering.<ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]" /><ref name="Low-Energy Nuclear Reactions Sourcebook" /><ref name=ICCF-17 /><ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion" /> In April 1972 he completed his doctorate degree in Engineering at Hokkaido University, Faculty of Engineering, Department of Engineering.<ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]" /><ref name="Low-Energy Nuclear Reactions Sourcebook" /><ref name=ICCF-17 /><ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion" /> In March 1976, he received his doctorate in Engineering for "Study on formation process of hydride on the surface of Ti by d, n reaction” Teaching; Atomic Engineering, Corrosion, X-rays analysis, Electron microscope, Exercise: Mathematics, Physical Engineering.<ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion [Hardcover]" /><ref name="Low-Energy Nuclear Reactions Sourcebook" /><ref name=ICCF-17 /><ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion" />
==Awards== He was awarded [[The International Society for Condensed Matter Nuclear Science Prizes]] ([[Giuliano Preparata]] medal) in 2004 from The International Society for Condensed Matter Nuclear Science (ISCMNS).<ref name="Giuliano Preparata Medal">{{cite web|last=Giuliano Preparata Medal|first=Winners|title=Giuliano Preparata Medal|url=http://www.iscmns.org/prizes.htm|work=The International Society for Condensed MatterNuclear Science|publisher=The International Society for Condensed Matter Nuclear Science|accessdate=8 February 2013}}</ref><ref name=ICCF-17 /> The ISCMNS is the organizer of a conference and a workshop on [[cold fusion]] and related topics.
==Publications== *"Sorption of Hydrogen On and In Hydrogen Absorbing Metal in Electrochemical Environments" (Plenum Press)<ref name=ICCF-17 /><ref name="Hokkaido University">{{cite web|last=Faculty and Graduate School of Engineering,|first=Hokkaido University|title=Article|url=http://nms.qe.eng.hokudai.ac.jp/contents/article/article_e.html|work=Laboratory of Nuclear and Environmental Materials|publisher=Hokkaido University Laboratory of Nuclear Material Systems 2003|accessdate=14 February 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130413113634/http://nms.qe.eng.hokudai.ac.jp/contents/article/article_e.html|archivedate=13 April 2013|df=}}</ref> *"An understanding of the environment, Global environment and the human life” (Sankyo Publishing, in 2006)<ref name=ICCF-17 /><ref name="Kankyō no rikai : chikyū kankyō to ningen seikatsu.">{{cite web|last=WorldCat|title=Kankyō no rikai: chikyū kankyō to ningen seikatsu.|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/kankyo-no-rikai-chikyu-kankyo-to-ningen-seikatsu/oclc/76918251|isbn= 978-4-7827-0517-9}}</ref> *"Low Energy Nuclear Reactions Sourcebook" (American Chemical Society, in 2008)<ref name="Low-Energy Nuclear Reactions Sourcebook">{{cite web|last=ACS Symposium Series|title=Low-Energy Nuclear Reactions Sourcebook|url=http://pubs.acs.org/isbn/9780841269668|isbn= 978-0-8412-6966-8|publisher=2013 American Chemical Society|accessdate=14 February 2013}}</ref><ref name=ICCF-17 /> *"Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion" (Infinite Energy Press, in 1998)<ref name=ICCF-17 /><ref name="Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion">{{cite web|last=Infinite Energy|title=Nuclear Transmutation: The Reality of Cold Fusion|url=http://www.infinite-energy.com/iemagazine/issue17/bookreview_mizuno.html|work=Book Review|publisher=Infinite Energy Magazine|accessdate=14 February 2013}}</ref>
==Academic societies== * The International Society for Condensed Matter Nuclear Science<ref name="ISCMNS List of Members">{{cite web|title=ISCMNS List of Members|url=http://www.iscmns.org/admin/list_of_members.htm|work=List of Members|publisher=ISCMNS|accessdate=18 March 2013}}</ref> * International Hydrogen Energy Society<ref name=ICCF-17 /> * International Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics<ref name=ICCF-17 /> * Atomic Energy Society of Japan<ref name=ICCF-17 /> * [[Japan Society of Applied Physics]]<ref name=ICCF-17 /> * Japan Cold Fusion Research Society<ref name="JCF List of Founders">{{cite web|title=JCF List of Founders|url=http://www.jcfrs.org/infoe.html|work=List of Founders|publisher=JCF Research Society|accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref>
==Research activities== Electrochemical, metallurgy, nuclear reaction in condensed matter, elucidation of the peculiar behavior of hydrogen in the metal, hydrogen penetration in metals, hydrogen embrittlement, hydrogen production, hydrogen separation and purification, power conversion of hydrogen, elucidation of hydrogen behavior, development of unique methods using hydrogen isotopes, studying the behavior of hydrogen on metal. Mizuno has also written Numerous books representing the interaction between hydrogen and the metals.<ref name=ReaD&Researchmap>{{cite web|last=Researchmap|title=ReaD&Researchmap|url=http://researchmap.jp/read0166652/?lang=english|work=National Institute of Informatics (NII)|publisher=National Institute of Informatics (NII)|accessdate=8 February 2013}}</ref><ref name=ICCF-17 />
==Extramural activities== Mizuno was involved in anti-terrorism measures as part of international safety measures for [[Hakodate]] Customs of [[Ministry of Finance (Japan)|Ministry of Finance]].<ref name=ICCF-17 />{{Clarify|date=February 2013}}
